Messenger: sample application to learn Play! 2
==============================================

Messenger application.

Heroku:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11510256/deploy-a-play-2-0-2-application-on-heroku
	heroku config:add BUILDPACK_URL=https://github.com/heroku/heroku-buildpack-scala.git --app your_app_name

add heroku remote 

Set up keys. 

	heroku keys

generates some keys in Linux (in windows it failed), but due to some reason I can't use it. Added existing key with:

	heroku keys:add ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 

(linux only:)
http://www.betaful.com/2011/01/i-love-git-subtree/
	git clone https://github.com/apenwarr/git-subtree.git
	cd git-subtree
	sudo ./install.sh 

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7539382/how-can-i-deploy-from-a-git-subdirectory
	git subtree push --prefix play/messenger heroku master
or just use messenger_heroku_deploy.sh from learning project root
If screwed up and then fixed local version then use messenger_heroku_force_deploy.sh

See running instances:
$ heroku ps
See log:
$ heroku logs
Set instances number:
$ heroku ps:scale web=1
Open application in browser:
$ heroku open
	
May need to set up DATABASE_URL manually (also may need to delete default DB):
$ heroku addons:add heroku-postgresql:dev
$ heroku config 
(get variable name for following step)
$ heroku pg:promote HEROKU_POSTGRESQL_RED_URL

